<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1150,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName box="[151,334,1150,1174]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ravulus">
<emphasis box="[151,334,1150,1174]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Colletes ravulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Noskiewicz" box="[542,758,1150,1174]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Noskiewicz, J. (1936) Die Palearktischen Colletes - Arten. Wydawnictwo Towarzystwa Naukowego we Lwowie, Lwow, v + 532 pp .. (Prace Naukowe, ser. 2, No. 3)," type="book" year="1936">
Noskiewicz (
<number box="[690,750,1150,1174]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1936.0">1936</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, based on a single male collected 
<number box="[1141,1197,1150,1174]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1892.0">1892</number>
by Leder in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,263,1186,1210]" name="Mongolia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[332,380,1187,1211]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">type</typeStatus>
is lost (
<bibRefCitation author="Kuhlmann" box="[479,670,1186,1210]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Kuhlmann, M. (2000) Katalog der palaarktischen Arten der Bienengattung Colletes Latr., mit Lectotypenfestlegungen, neuer Synonymie und der Beschreibung von zwei neuen Arten (Hymenoptera: Apidae: Colletinae). Linzer biologische Beitrage, 32 (1), 155 - 193." type="journal article" year="2000">
Kuhlmann 
<number box="[610,670,1186,1210]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but the detailed description and the characteristically shaped S 
<number box="[1422,1436,1186,1210]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="7.0">7</number>
enabled the unambiguous identification of three males collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[907,982,1222,1246]" name="Russia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Russia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1038,1147,1222,1246]" name="Mongolia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
as 
<taxonomicName box="[1185,1302,1222,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ravulus">
<emphasis box="[1185,1302,1222,1246]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. ravulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. One of the males was collected together with the hitherto unknown female that is described below. Another female was identified from material in the Institute of Zoology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1150,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
To facilitate the identification of this little-known species, illustrations of taxonomically relevant morphological features of the male are provided (
<figureCitation box="[575,643,1366,1390]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,303,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,303,1843]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, male: a. head, showing the smooth and shiny end of the clypeus; b. finely striate malar area; c. metasomal terga 1 and 2; d. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view); e. genitalia (dorsal view); f. gonostylus (lateral view). Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278973/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Figs 
<number box="[631,643,1366,1390]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
a–f) and the female is described below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,286,1403,1427]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1150,2003]" box="[199,286,1403,1427]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1403,1427]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1150,2003]" box="[199,314,1438,1463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1438,1463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1150,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
In the female of 
<taxonomicName box="[384,500,1475,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ravulus">
<emphasis box="[384,500,1475,1499]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. ravulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the punctation of T 
<number box="[725,735,1474,1498]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1.0">1</number>
is fine and dense (i &lt;d) (
<figureCitation box="[1021,1088,1474,1498]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[1074,1088,1474,1498]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
f), a character only shared with 
<taxonomicName box="[151,300,1510,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perforator">
<emphasis box="[151,300,1510,1534]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. perforator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[314,395,1510,1534]" captionStart="FIGURE 22. a" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1758,1781]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,194,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[151,1436,193,1737]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 22. a. Colletes patellatus Pérez, female: head; b. metasomal terga 1 and 2; c. C. perforator Smith, female: head; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2; e. C. impunctatus Nylander, female: head; f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278990/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[366,395,1510,1534]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
d) and 
<taxonomicName box="[470,613,1510,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patellatus">
<emphasis box="[470,613,1510,1534]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. patellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[627,708,1510,1534]" captionStart="FIGURE 22. a" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1758,1781]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,194,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[151,1436,193,1737]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 22. a. Colletes patellatus Pérez, female: head; b. metasomal terga 1 and 2; c. C. perforator Smith, female: head; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2; e. C. impunctatus Nylander, female: head; f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278990/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[679,708,1510,1534]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
b) within the 
<taxonomicName box="[856,969,1510,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fodiens">
<emphasis box="[856,969,1510,1534]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. fodiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. However, the apical tergal hair bands of 
<taxonomicName box="[308,426,1547,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ravulus">
<emphasis box="[308,426,1547,1571]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. ravulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are much broader than in these species (
<figureCitation box="[890,959,1546,1570]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[944,959,1546,1570]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
e), allowing for a reliable identification of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1150,2003]" box="[199,337,1618,1643]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1618,1643]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1150,2003]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Bl = 10.0–11.0 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[439,503,1655,1679]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Head</emphasis>
. L = 2.8–2.9 mm; W = 3.6–3.7 mm. Head wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[1202,1272,1654,1678]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[1257,1272,1654,1678]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Integument black except tips of mandible partly dark reddish-brown. Face except clypeus densely covered with long, whitishgrey, erect hairs. Clypeus and supraclypeal area convex in profile. Clypeus finely and densely punctate and without a median depression; surface between punctures shiny (
<figureCitation box="[783,852,1762,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[837,852,1762,1786]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Supraclypeal area medially impunctate, laterally with a few, small punctures; surface medially shiny, laterally less so and slightly shagreened. Malar area medially about ¼ as long as width of mandible base, finely striate. Antenna black. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[977,1103,1835,1859]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc between punctures smooth and shiny; disc sparsely punctate (i = 2.0–3.0d) (
<figureCitation box="[1102,1171,1870,1894]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[1155,1171,1870,1894]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
c). Scutellum anteriorly sparsely punctate with more dense punctation apically, surface smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation box="[1063,1131,1906,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[1115,1131,1906,1930]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
c). Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum covered with yellowish-white erect hairs. Basal area of propodeum as illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[298,364,1978,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[349,364,1978,2002]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
d. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[391,466,1978,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Wings</emphasis>
. Hyaline; wing venation dark brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[891,947,1979,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Legs</emphasis>
. Integument black. Vestiture whitish, scopa white. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[230,354,152,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Metasoma</emphasis>
. Integument black except narrow apical margins of T brownish translucent; T 
<number box="[1268,1278,151,175]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1.0">1</number>
to T 
<number box="[1340,1352,151,175]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="3.0">3</number>
with a slight oily-bluish shine. T 
<number box="[440,450,188,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1.0">1</number>
sparsely covered with short to long, partly appressed white hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1186,1253,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[1238,1253,188,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
f); discs of T 
<number box="[1394,1408,188,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="2.0">2</number>
to T 
<number box="[168,181,223,247]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="6.0">6</number>
without white hairs; apical tergal hair bands broad (
<figureCitation box="[765,833,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[817,833,223,247]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
e). Terga densely and finely punctate (i &lt;d) (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1404,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[1389,1404,223,247]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
f).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
